#X text 295 327 THIS IS BEING LEFT THE WAY IT IS FOR AN IMPORTANT REASON. This does not work very well because of the part that randomly selects the two different settings made by the message boxes that turn the audio level on and off. Turning the audio level off just by clicking the off message box or on by clicking the on message box is not the problem. The problme. The problem is when the on message box is selected twice in a row or more times. At that point \, the ramp formed by the [line~] goes back to 0 but it goes back to 0 from whatever level is specified by the on message box. The original intent of the message boxes was to avoid the sudden jump up to a volume level from 0 or the sudden drop from a volume level to 0 It is those sudden jumps that produce audible clicks which are not only undesirable in instances where they are not part of a rhythm \, they can also harm an audio system.;
